(108, 'Emergency WASH Response to COVID-19 for Province2\r\nMonthly Progress Report', ''),
(110, 'Tornado Response and Recovery project, 2019 Nepal ', '<p>Tornado Response and Recovery project, 2019 Nepal project is funded by Caritas Nepal from 15th July 2019 to 30th Feb 2021. The project aim to support the Tornado Affected households of Bara district of province 2.&nbsp;</p><p>ï‚— Total 536 people participated in this campaign, Male 240, Female 296 including Dalit 18, Janjati 113, Muslim 16 and OBC 389. &nbsp;</p><p>ï‚— Six-step of hand washing was demonstrated in 3 schools. 160 students, teachers, and members of School management committee practiced and become aware on sanitation and personal hygiene in their life. &nbsp;</p><p>â€¢ 206 school students received 206 WASH kit, each kit containing one towel, one soap, one bottle of oil, one tooth paste, one tooth cleaner, and one nail cutter</p><p>â€¢ 156 community people made the commitment and clean their community and school.</p><p>â€¢ 20 people got training on mobile repairing and they advanced their knowledge and skill on mobile repairing. The best five trainees also get grant support of NPR 20,000.00 each to start mobile repairing shop.</p><p>â€¢ The beneficiaries have started different types of business/microenterprises like Kirana shop (1), selling fast food in Rikshaw (1), selling dry fish (1), selling cosmetic items (2), selling fast food static place (4) and selling vegetable (1).They have improved their livelihood, secure their income and obtain their financial income NPR 300 to 1000 per day.</p><p>â€¢ They increased their knowledge and practice on selection of land for vegetable cultivation, nursery preparation, seeding method, seasonal and off-season vegetable production, prevention and control of insects by organic methods as well as marketing their products. &nbsp;</p><p>â€¢ They received 36 spray tank, fertilizer (DAP 6221 KG, Urea 4116 KG, Potash 1257 KG, Safaya/Fungicide 38 Packets. &nbsp;</p><p>â€¢ 65 beneficiaries got 1822 cemented tiles and used in house repairing.</p>'),
(111, 'COVID-19 Emergency Response project', '<p>The COVID-19 Emergency Response Project is supported by Caritas Nepal for emergency response during the covid-19 pandemic. 100 HHs of daily wage earners of Mahagadhimai Municipality-7 Bara and 150 HHs of Devatal Rural Municipality-7 &nbsp;Bara have been supported by relief food items like rice, pulse, cooking oil, salt and soap.&nbsp;</p>'),
(113, 'Early Grade Quality Improvement Project', '<p><strong>Project Name: </strong>Early Grade Quality Improvement Project.</p><p><strong>Donor:</strong> Ukaid/VSO Nepal</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 January 2021-31st March 2022.</p><p><strong>Budget:</strong> NPR 4186056</p><p>JJYC Bara has been implementing Early Grade Quality Improvement Project (EQUIP) supported and funded by FCDO with partnership of VSO Nepal from Jan-March 2021 in four local levels of Bara and Rautahat Districts. The project is aligned with the SAHAYATRA project funded by European Union and led by VSO. The project aims to ensure inclusive quality education for marginalized girls and children with disability through resilient, gender-responsive education governance enhanced by CSO engagement in Nepal. The project is being implemented in 20 schools of Bara and Rautahat district respectively. 10 schools were selected from Bara district i.e. 5 schools each from Kalaiya and Jeetpur-Simara sub-metropolitan city of Bara district and 10 schools were selected from two municipalities of Rautahat district i.e Gadhi Mai Municipality and Gaur Municipality. The EQUIP is currently focused on Development and enhancement of ECD at school and municipal level of both districts.&nbsp;</p>');

